1. PROBLEM STATEMENT
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Support teams at HackerRank, Claude, and Visa receive hundreds
of tickets daily. Many are simple FAQs; some are sensitive,
risky, or out-of-scope. Manual triage is slow and error-prone.

We need an AI agent that:
  - Reads a CSV of support tickets
  - Understands which company/domain it belongs to
  - Retrieves relevant info from a local corpus only
  - Decides: reply with a grounded answer OR escalate to human
  - Outputs a structured CSV with 5 fields per ticket

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2. GOALS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
G1. Process all tickets in support_issues.csv accurately
G2. Never hallucinate policies or unsupported claims
G3. Escalate all high-risk / sensitive / ambiguous tickets
G4. Produce clean, structured output.csv
G5. Terminal-based execution (python code/main.py)
G6. Modern graphical terminal UI using Rich library
G7. Log all AI interactions to ~/hackerrank_orchestrate/log.txt
G8. Zero cost — no API keys requiring credit card

