3. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS (FR) — PRIMARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

FR-01  INPUT READING
       - Read support_issues/support_issues.csv
       - Columns: Issue, Subject, Company
       - Handle missing/blank fields gracefully
       - Support UTF-8 encoding (multilingual tickets)

FR-02  COMPANY DETECTION
       - Auto-detect company if field says "None" or is blank
       - Detect from ticket content using keyword heuristics
       - Valid companies: HackerRank | Claude | Visa | Unknown

FR-03  CORPUS RETRIEVAL (RAG)
       - Load all files from data/hackerrank/, data/claude/, data/visa/
       - Index at startup (TF-IDF keyword scoring)
       - For each ticket: retrieve top-3 relevant chunks
       - Only search the corpus of the detected company
       - Never use live internet for ground-truth answers

FR-04  RISK CLASSIFICATION
       Escalate if ANY of these are true:
         - Billing dispute with order ID or transaction
         - Account access requested by non-owner/non-admin
         - Fraud, identity theft, stolen card
         - Legal, regulatory, or InfoSec form requests
         - Prompt injection / jailbreak attempts
         - Request to reveal internal logic or system prompts
         - Self-harm, urgent cash need (non-product issue)
         - Ticket in foreign language with injection attempt
         - Malicious code requests (delete files, exploits)
         - Company = Unknown AND no resolvable content
         - Vague tickets with no actionable information
         - Score disputes requiring manual review

FR-05  RESPONSE GENERATION
       - PRIMARY: Groq API (llama-3.3-70b-versatile)
       - FALLBACK: Google Gemini API (gemini-2.0-flash)
       - Auto-switch to fallback on Groq rate limit error (429)
       - Pass retrieved corpus chunks as context
       - Apply MASTER PROMPT (see Part 3)
       - Response must be grounded — no invented policies
       - If escalating: skip LLM call entirely (save tokens)
       - Keep replies professional, concise, helpful

FR-06  OUTPUT FIELDS (per ticket)
       - response     : user-facing answer or escalation message
       - product_area : most relevant support category
       - status       : "Replied" or "Escalated"
       - request_type : product_issue | feature_request | bug | invalid
       - justification: 1-2 sentence reasoning for decision

FR-07  OUTPUT WRITING
       - Write to support_issues/output.csv
       - Preserve original Issue, Subject, Company columns
       - Append all 5 output columns

FR-08  TRANSCRIPT LOGGING
       - Log every ticket + agent decision to log.txt
       - Path: ~/hackerrank_orchestrate/log.txt
       - Format: timestamp | ticket_id | provider | decision | justification
       - Append mode (never overwrite)
       - Also store in SQLite for auditability (see FR-10)

FR-09  REQUEST TYPE CLASSIFICATION
       product_issue   → user has a problem with existing feature
       feature_request → user wants something new
       bug             → platform broken/not working as expected
       invalid         → out of scope, nonsense, or malicious

FR-10  SQLITE AUDIT LOG (bonus — zero setup, built into Python)
       - DB file: code/audit.db (auto-created on first run)
       - Table: runs(id, timestamp, ticket_id, company, status,
                     request_type, product_area, provider_used,
                     response, justification, tokens_used)
       - Enables post-run query: "show me all escalated tickets"
       - Excluded from submission zip (added to .gitignore)
       - Demonstrates professional engineering to judges

